==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obliquely
<hw>Ob*lique"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In an oblique manner; not
directly; indirectly.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Truth <xex>obliquely</xex>
leveled.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bp. Fell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Declining from the noon of day,⟦br⟧
The sun <qex>obliquely</qex> shoots his burning ray.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His discourse tends <qex>obliquely</qex> to the detracting from
others.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obliqueness</ent>⟦br⟧
